Older adults with multiple myeloma (MM) are a growing population, and 
personalizing treatment based on disease and health status is imperative. 
Similar to MM staging systems that provide disease-related prognostic 
information, myeloma-specific frailty tools can better identify subgroups at 
greatest risk for treatment-related toxicity and early treatment 
discontinuation, as well as predict overall survival. Several myeloma-specific 
validated tools are well studied. Although these fitness/frailty scores have 
